title: Breast Cancer [SH46926_Cell3]
characteristics_ch1.1: patient diagnosis: Breast Cancer
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.

characteristics_ch1.1: patient diagnosis: Breast Cancer
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.

extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.

Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: Glioma

extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: HCC

Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.

extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: Pancreatic Cancer

Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: Malignant bone and soft tissue tumor

characteristics_ch1.1: patient diagnosis: Malignant bone and soft tissue tumor
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.

label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.

extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: Malignant bone and soft tissue tumor

Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: Malignant bone and soft tissue tumor

characteristics_ch1.1: patient diagnosis: Malignant bone and soft tissue tumor
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.

label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: Benign bone and soft tissue tumor

extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: Intermediate bone and soft tissue tumor

extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.

data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: Intermediate bone and soft tissue tumor

extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: Intermediate bone and soft tissue tumor

label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: Malignant bone and soft tissue tumor

characteristics_ch1.1: patient diagnosis: Benign bone and soft tissue tumor
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.

label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.

extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
patient diagnosis:ch1: Healthy

label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.

label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.

label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.

characteristics_ch1.1: patient diagnosis: Healthy
extract_protocol_ch1: Total RNA was extracted each from 300uL serum samples using 3D-Gene® RNA extraction reagent from liquid sample kit (Toray Industries, Inc.). Total RNA was also obtained from the FFPE sections using the Arcturus® Paradise® Extraction and Isolation kit (Life Technologies) in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
label_protocol_ch1: miRNA was labeled using 3D-Gene® miRNA Labeling kit in accordance with the manufacturer's instructions.
hyb_protocol: Hybridized for 16 h at 32 ºC with rotary shaker (250 rpm). Hybridization buffer and washing protocol was attached in the 3D-Gene® miRNA oligo chip kit.
scan_protocol: 3D-Gene® Scanner (Toray Industries, Inc.) was used for scanning. Images were quantified using Extraction version 2.0.0.6 (Toray Industries, Inc.).
data_processing: Mean and standard deviation (SD) of the 5% trimmed signals of the negative controls were calculated. Signals of miRNAs over mean+2SD of the negative controls were subtracted with the mean of the negative controls. The undetected signal was replaced with the value that was the least signal intensity on each DNA chip minus 0.1 in log2 scale followed by quantile normalization.
